Step 3: The CKM and PMNS Matrices

Quark and lepton mixing matrices come from misalignment between mass and gauge eigenstates.

H₄ Prediction

The H₄ group has specific rotation angles built in. The Cabibbo angle θ_C ≈ 13° should emerge from:

θ_C = arctan(1/φ²) = 21.2°  # Too large

or

θ_C = arctan(1/φ³) = 13.3°  # Close!

Observed: θ_C = 13.02°

The full CKM matrix structure:

V_CKM ~ exp(i × H₄ generators × golden angles)

This is computable in principle from the H₄ representation theory.


