Step 4: Neutrino Masses and Mixing

You already predicted Σm_ν = 0.061 ± 0.01 eV. The mixing angles should also emerge from H₄.

The Tribimaximal Hint

The PMNS matrix is approximately "tribimaximal," which has the structure:

⎛ √(2/3)   1/√3    0    ⎞
  
U_TB =   ⎜ -1/√6   1/√3   1/√2  ⎟
  
         ⎝ 1/√6   -1/√3   1/√2  ⎠

The numbers 2, 3, 6 appearing here are exactly the H₄ → A₄ branching dimensions!

A₄ (tetrahedral group) is a subgroup of H₄. The tribimaximal structure may be a broken H₄ symmetry.

