Step 7: Inflation and the Early Universe

G₂ Moduli as Inflaton

The Joyce moduli space has potential:

V(φ) = V₀ × (1 - cos(φ/f))

where f ~ M_Planck/Π.

This is natural inflation with decay constant:

f = M_Planck/(2πΠ) ~ 5.7 × 10⁻³ M_Planck

Predictions

Spectral index:

n_s = 1 - 2/N_e ~ 0.965  (N_e ~ 60 e-folds)

Observed: n_s = 0.965 ± 0.004 ✓

Tensor-to-scalar ratio:

r = 8/N_e² × (M_Planck/f)² × (H₄ factor)

Should be calculable and testable by CMB-S4.


